    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.20.17-20a_0001" />
                <fw type="curatorial">17</fw>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
<address><addrLine>Skyrim Farm,</addrLine>
                <addrLine>Route 6,</addrLine>
                <addrLine>Columbia, Mo.</addrLine></address>
                
                <date>8-23-'55.</date>
                    </dateline>
                
                <salute>Dear Kendrick:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>That was a precious letter &#8212; bless your warm heart!</p>
                
                <p>It is good to hear about your children &#8212; all of them fine young people, and going places, "high-hearted with a hunger for the new". I feel deeply all you 
                    <hi rend="underline">say</hi> of them, and <hi rend="underline">what can</hi> <hi rend="italic">not</hi> <hi rend="underline">be said</hi> even more. How very worthwhile it all is!</p>
               
                <p>Things go well here, as usual. Nice, spangly Xmas with five (5) grandchildren to furnish the enthusiasm and sense of wonder. We do not think of
                    
                  
                    <note type="authorial">(over)</note>
                    <note type="curatorial">WESTERN HISTORICAL MANUSCRIPTS COLLECTION
                        UNIVERSITY OF MISSOURI
                        COLUMBIA, MO.</note>
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.20.17-20a_0002"/>
                    
                    <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                    <fw type="curatorial">18</fw>
                    the celebrations as applying only to the Christ story (a symbol of tremendous meaning in itself). Surely it has a wholly non-sectarian <hi rend="underline">cosmic</hi> significance that was profoundly felt long before the Christian era.</p>
                
                <p>Alice's horse business is growing rapidly. She has a riding school, as you may know. It is well patronized, but the horse raising and training is more important in the long run. She has 12 horses of her own and is boarding and training several others &#8212; with the help of Mr. "Dick" Cook of Stephens College. He is
                    <note type="curatorial">WESTERN HISTORICAL MANUSCRIPTS COLLECTION
                        UNIVERSITY OF MISSOURI
                        COLUMBIA, MISSOURI</note>
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.20.17-20a_0003"/>
                    
                   <fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>
                    <fw type="curatorial">19</fw>
                    
                    a master and an excellent influence for Alice. She is all fire and plunging &#8212; like the high-bred horses she handles. <hi rend="underline">He</hi> is <hi rend="underline">quiet, slow-moving, wise</hi>. (He is nearly 60 years old &amp; all his life has been spent with saddle horses). Alice has several really fine horses, and Mona &amp; I have one. Really top horses, <add>some of them,</add> with the very best bloodlines. Also, Mona &amp; I have four ponies &#8212; two of them mares with foal. We expect some beautiful colts in the spring.</p>
                
                <p>University classes are doing finely.</p>
                
                <p>This carries <del/> love to you. You are good and dear.</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>Your friend,</salute>
                <signed>John Neihardt</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="authorial">Mona &amp; Alice send kindest thoughts (over)</note>
                <note type="curatorial">WESTERN HISTORICAL MANUSCRIPT COLLECT<unclear reason="missing" cert="high">ION</unclear>
                UNIVERSITY OF MISSOURI
                COLUMBIA, MO.</note>
                <pb facs="nei.20.17-20a_0004"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">20</fw>
                
                   <postscript><p>We have remodelled the barn with 14 box stalls. Also, we have a good riding ring.</p>
                   
                   <note type="curatorial">WESTERN HISTORICAL MANUSCRIPTS
                   UNIVERSITY OF MISSOURI
                   COLUMBIA, MO.</note>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.20.17-20a_0005"/>
                       <fw type="curatorial">20a</fw>
                      
                    <p>Your brother and I have many a good talk out in front of Jesse Hall during the noon hour.</p></postscript>
                <note type="curatorial">WESTERN HISTORICAL MANUSCRIPTS COLLECTION
                UNIVERSITY OF MISSOURI
                COLUMBIA, MO.</note>
            </div1>
